=== Cultural Properties ===
=== Shibukawa City Designated Important Tangible Cultural Property ===
* Kawasukune Shrine {{ill|lt=Sangaku|Q2569069|qid=Q2569069|1=Sangaku}} (designated January 30, Showa 50)<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=Designated Cultural Properties of Former Shibukawa City Area |website=www.city.shibukawa.lg.jp |access-date=2024-08-20 |language=ja}}</ref> – Measuring 190 cm in width and 80 cm in height, it was dedicated in {{ill|lt=Ansei|Q1327259|qid=Q1327259|1=Ansei}} 3 ({{ill|lt=1856|Q7676|qid=Q7676|1=1856}}) by Chiaki Keietsu, a native of Tsukiji Village, {{ill|lt=Tone District|Q1077001|qid=Q1077001|1=Tone District, Gunma}} (present-day {{ill|lt=Katashina Village|Q1203661|qid=Q1203661|1=Katashina, Gunma}}). The sangaku calculates the base length of a right triangle using algebra{{Sfn|Shibukawa City History Compilation Committee|1986|pp=273-274}}.

=== Shibukawa City Designated Important Intangible Cultural Property ===
* Kawashima {{ill|lt=Lion Dance|Q713866|qid=Q713866|1=Lion dance}} (designated October 20, Showa 47) – A ritual performed by the Kawashima Lion Dance Preservation Society to pray for warding off evil, good health, and abundant harvests. It is dedicated at the annual festival of the subordinate Suwa Shrine (early October)<ref name=":0" />. Though believed to have been interrupted by the eruption of Mount Asama in Tenmei 3 (1783), an extant storage box for the lion heads bears the date {{ill|lt=Tenpō|Q1369045|qid=Q1369045|1=Tenpō}} 4 ({{ill|lt=1833|Q7587|qid=Q7587|1=1833}}), suggesting it was revived around that time. The dance is performed by a single dancer wearing a waist drum, and the lion heads consist of three types: male lion (Hōgan), female lion, and child lion{{Sfn|Shibukawa City History Compilation Committee|1986|pp=299-230}}.

=== Access ===
* 15-minute walk from {{ill|lt=Kanashima Station (Gunma Prefecture)|Q6360686|qid=Q6360686|lt=Kanashima Station|1=Kanashima Station}} on the {{ill|lt=Agatsuma Line|Q391568|qid=Q391568|1=Agatsuma Line}} of {{ill|lt=East Japan Railway Company|Q499071|qid=Q499071|lt=JR East|1=East Japan Railway Company}}

